<item>
            <title>[GROOVY-2515] Command line option -D does not work in Windows XP but does in MacOSX</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-2515</link>
                <project id="12318123" key="GROOVY">Groovy</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In WindowsXP...&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Z:\dev&amp;gt;gant -D barney=123&lt;br/&gt;
Target 123 does not exist.&lt;br/&gt;
Z:\dev&amp;gt;gant -D barney=abc&lt;br/&gt;
Target abc does not exist.&lt;br/&gt;
Z:\dev&amp;gt;gant -D barney=&quot;abc&quot;&lt;br/&gt;
Target abc does not exist.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In MacOSX&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;$ gant -D barney=123&lt;br/&gt;
123&lt;br/&gt;
     &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;echo&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; 123&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt;Example Gant file:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;target ( main : &apos;A target&apos; ) {&lt;br/&gt;
  println barney&lt;br/&gt;
  echo ( message : barney )&lt;br/&gt;
}&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;setDefaultTarget ( main )&lt;/p&gt;</description>
